03:53.100 --> 03:55.000
Allison, look.
Whatever you saw...

03:55.000 --> 03:55.900
Our daughter, Joe.

03:55.900 --> 03:58.900
The danger is not imminent,
if it's even real.

03:58.900 --> 04:00.200
What does that mean?

04:00.200 --> 04:04.200
Come on. The reality is,
Ariel does not dri.

04:04.400 --> 04:05.100
Yet!

04:05.100 --> 04:06.300
Exactly.

04:06.700 --> 04:07.600
Whatever you saw,

04:07.600 --> 04:10.300
it has nothing to do
with the here and now.

04:10.400 --> 04:12.300
I mean, you know as well as I do

04:12.400 --> 04:14.100
she's a good
two-and-a-half years away

04:14.100 --> 04:15.600
from getting behind the wheel
of a car.

04:15.600 --> 04:16.700
So?

04:16.700 --> 04:18.200
So there's still time

04:18.700 --> 04:20.899
to make sure
that it doesn't happen.

04:21.000 --> 04:22.400
In fact, we can guarantee it.

04:22.400 --> 04:23.800
What do you mean, guarantee it?

04:23.800 --> 04:25.800
What kind of car
did she have
the accident in?

04:26.900 --> 04:28.400
I have no idea.

04:28.500 --> 04:30.900
Okay. Well, hopefully,
sometime in the next

04:30.900 --> 04:32.900
two-and-a-half years,
you'll have this dream again.

04:33.000 --> 04:34.200
And maybe then
you'll make it a point

04:34.200 --> 04:36.300
to notice what make
and model the car is.

04:36.300 --> 04:38.000
Then we'll make it a point
never to buy

04:38.000 --> 04:39.100
that make
or model car.

04:39.100 --> 04:40.700
Well, maybe it's not our car.

04:40.700 --> 04:43.300
Maybe she borrows it
from a friend or a boyfriend.

04:43.300 --> 04:46.400
Okay, fine. Fine. Look. When and
if you know what kind

04:46.400 --> 04:48.200
of car it is, then
we'll both just go

04:48.200 --> 04:50.100
to Ariel and
we'll tell her.

04:51.500 --> 04:53.700
And she'll make it her business
never to get in one,

04:53.700 --> 04:55.100
much less drive one.

04:58.800 --> 05:02.200
See? It's a lock.
It's a guarantee.

05:05.700 --> 05:07.500
Come on. Let's
get some rest.

05:07.800 --> 05:11.000
CYNTHIA KEENER:
She's 16 years old.
Her name's Melanie Daniels.

05:11.300 --> 05:13.200
Apparently, she's
a very good kid.

05:13.200 --> 05:15.400
No history of
trouble or drugs.

05:15.400 --> 05:19.300
She's a junior at
Hilldale High School
across town.

05:19.800 --> 05:22.000
She's been missing
since yesterday morning.

05:22.400 --> 05:24.100
She caught the bus
to go to school

05:24.100 --> 05:26.000
but never showed
up at school.

05:27.800 --> 05:29.700
This happened yesterday?

05:30.000 --> 05:31.400
Why? Is something
the matter?

05:32.400 --> 05:33.700
I guess I'm just surprised

05:33.700 --> 05:36.000
that her parents called you
before the police.

05:36.000 --> 05:38.100
Oh, no, no.
They-They didn't call me.

05:38.100 --> 05:39.300
I called them.

05:39.900 --> 05:42.100
I went over to their home,
actually.

05:42.600 --> 05:45.900
Just as soon as the missing
child report came through

05:45.900 --> 05:48.000
on my e-mail, 
I drove over and talked

05:48.000 --> 05:50.600
to the mother, and explained
that while

05:51.200 --> 05:53.700
there were several hundred cases
the police were tracking,

05:53.700 --> 05:55.800
for me, this would
be the only one.

06:00.100 --> 06:02.800
That's quite a look
on your face, Mrs. Dubois.

06:04.100 --> 06:05.900
I'm not an ambulance chaser,

06:06.300 --> 06:07.900
but this <i>is</i> how I make my money,

06:07.900 --> 06:11.100
and I need to strike
while the iron's hot.

06:15.500 --> 06:16.600
Okay.

06:16.600 --> 06:19.000
Um... forgive me.

06:19.000 --> 06:21.000
I'm not certain
how this works.

06:21.100 --> 06:25.100
But I've read online
that people like you,

06:25.400 --> 06:26.700
when they
touch something

06:26.800 --> 06:30.100
that belongs to
a missing person or,

06:30.400 --> 06:31.900
for instance,
a dead person,

06:32.300 --> 06:35.800
um, sometimes you...
you might get vibes

06:35.800 --> 06:37.800
or signals.

06:39.600 --> 06:40.800
Yes? No?

06:43.700 --> 06:45.400
Sometimes. It depends.

06:48.300 --> 06:51.500
Here's the entire contents
of Melanie's locker.

06:51.700 --> 06:53.900
Her mother gave me
permission to borrow it.

06:53.900 --> 06:54.700
I was wondering

06:54.700 --> 06:58.300
if you could do, uh...
whatever it is that you do,

06:58.300 --> 07:00.500
and give me a call.

07:04.200 --> 07:05.600
Hey, Ariel.

07:06.100 --> 07:09.400
Are the Suns going to
make the playoffs this year?

07:09.500 --> 07:10.400
I don't know.

07:10.600 --> 07:11.800
I don't really follow sports.

07:11.800 --> 07:15.000
Well, maybe you
could ask your mom.

07:15.300 --> 07:18.000
I mean, she knows
the future, right?

07:18.000 --> 07:20.000
Come on, man.
No, no. no.
Just ask her

07:20.000 --> 07:21.300
if she could check
her crystal ball.

07:21.300 --> 07:22.700
Leave her alone, Jeremy.

07:22.700 --> 07:23.900
Just ask her.

07:28.100 --> 07:28.900
Ariel!

07:28.900 --> 07:30.000
Ariel, wait.

07:33.900 --> 07:35.200
What do you want, Connor?

07:36.400 --> 07:37.500
I don't know.

07:38.100 --> 07:40.800
He's a jerk. And I'm a jerk
for hanging around him.

07:41.400 --> 07:42.900
I'm really sorry.

07:43.500 --> 07:45.200
Okay. I heard you.

07:47.300 --> 07:49.600
So, are you going
to that KHBX thing?

07:49.800 --> 07:50.800
What?

07:51.100 --> 07:53.800
KHBX. The radio station.

07:54.800 --> 07:57.400
They have that concert
at the Orpheum every year.

07:57.800 --> 07:59.900
There's, like,
a dozen different groups.

08:00.000 --> 08:01.700
It's on Saturday
during the day.

08:02.300 --> 08:03.900
Did you maybe
want a ticket?

08:04.800 --> 08:06.200
No. That's okay.

08:06.200 --> 08:08.300
I actually don't have the money
for that right now.

08:09.400 --> 08:12.000
No. No. I... I mean,

08:13.000 --> 08:14.600
I would buy it for you.

08:15.300 --> 08:17.100
We'd... we'd
go together.

08:52.100 --> 08:53.900
I'm just warning you.
We're back from school,

08:53.900 --> 08:55.300
and I need your help
with something.

08:55.300 --> 08:56.600
What are you talking about?

08:56.700 --> 08:57.900
Mom? Did Dad tell you?

08:57.900 --> 09:00.700
The most amazing thing happened
to me at school today.

09:00.700 --> 09:01.800
Well, tell me.

09:02.100 --> 09:04.000
This really cute guy-- I think
he's in the 11th grade--

09:04.000 --> 09:06.200
asked me to go to a concert with
him on Saturday

09:06.200 --> 09:07.700
at the Orpheum downtown.

09:10.100 --> 09:12.000
Are parents going
to this concert?

09:12.000 --> 09:13.100
No.

09:14.100 --> 09:15.800
And who is
this boy again?

09:16.200 --> 09:18.100
Connor. He's really nice.

09:18.100 --> 09:20.500
Yeah? But we don't
even know him.

09:21.400 --> 09:23.300
And you want to go downtown
into the city?

09:23.300 --> 09:25.800
It's during the day.
And how are you
going to get there?

09:25.800 --> 09:28.300
I don't know. We haven't
figured that out yet.

09:28.400 --> 09:31.000
Oh, honey, I don't know.
I think that your mommy and I

09:31.000 --> 09:32.200
are going to have
a problem with this.

09:32.200 --> 09:33.200
I'm 14.

09:33.200 --> 09:34.100
And he's 16.

09:34.100 --> 09:34.800
So?

09:34.800 --> 09:36.700
So we don't know him.

09:37.600 --> 09:39.400
He's so nice. Honest.

09:39.400 --> 09:40.400
And you know this how?

09:40.400 --> 09:42.700
Because I know it!
And, besides, it's a concert!

09:42.700 --> 09:45.300
They'll be tons of people.
Nothing is going to happen.

09:45.300 --> 09:47.500
And you know this because
you've been to so many concerts?

09:47.800 --> 09:49.500
You two are crazy!

09:49.700 --> 09:50.900
Crazy? Really?

09:51.500 --> 09:52.700
You know what
I've been doing all day?

09:52.700 --> 09:54.500
I've been trying
to find a missing girl,

09:54.600 --> 09:56.300
a couple of years older
than you.

09:56.700 --> 09:59.500
Gone. Vanished into thin air.

09:59.700 --> 10:01.800
Okay. So? I'm not her!

10:02.500 --> 10:04.400
And how did it happen?
Was she going to a concert?

10:04.400 --> 10:06.200
No. Actually,
she was going to school.

10:06.200 --> 10:09.300
Okay. Fine.
I'll stop going to school.

10:09.300 --> 10:11.600
Hey! You're not gonna get
your way by being a wise guy.

10:11.600 --> 10:12.800
What difference does it make?

10:12.800 --> 10:14.400
I'm not going
to get my way anyways.

10:23.200 --> 10:24.200
Ariel?

10:38.000 --> 10:39.000
Ariel.

10:42.600 --> 10:45.200
You know, no one is saying
you can't ever go to a concert

10:45.200 --> 10:46.800
without an adult.

10:47.600 --> 10:50.800
No one is saying that
you can't ever go out with boys.

10:52.600 --> 10:54.100
Just not this boy.

10:55.000 --> 10:57.000
Just not this Saturday.

11:00.400 --> 11:02.500
Honey, I know
how you feel.

11:03.100 --> 11:04.500
(phone rings in distance)
My mom wouldn't let me go

11:04.500 --> 11:07.000
to a concert alone
until I was 16.

11:07.300 --> 11:08.100
And you know what?

11:08.100 --> 11:09.700
When I finally went,

11:10.600 --> 11:12.300
I realized she was right.

11:16.200 --> 11:17.300
Hey, it's Cynthia Keener.

11:17.300 --> 11:20.100
She wanted to know if
you had anything for her.

11:20.100 --> 11:22.600
She said you'd know
what that meant.
Yeah.

11:22.600 --> 11:23.900
Tell her I'm still
working on it.

11:23.900 --> 11:26.300
Tell her I need to
call her back, please.

11:30.100 --> 11:31.700
Ariel...
(sniffles)

11:37.300 --> 11:38.500
Fine.

